.SH "NAME"
skb_cow \- copy header of skb when it is required
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'int\ skb_cow('u
.BI "int skb_cow(struct\ sk_buff\ *\ " "skb" ", unsigned\ int\ " "headroom" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIskb\fR
.RS 4
buffer to cow
.RE
.PP
\fIheadroom\fR
.RS 4
needed headroom
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
If the skb passed lacks sufficient headroom or its data part is shared, data is reallocated\&. If reallocation fails, an error is returned and original skb is not changed\&.
.PP
The result is skb with writable area skb\->head\&.\&.\&.skb\->tail and at least
\fIheadroom\fR
of space at head\&.
